{"id": "general_smoltalk_2300_802289", "question": "How many diagonals does a regular seven-sided polygon contain?", "answer": "In a regular $n$-sided polygon, each vertex is connected to $n-3$ other vertices by diagonals.\nSo, in a regular seven-sided polygon, each vertex is connected to $7-3=4$ other vertices by diagonals.\nHowever, we have to divide by 2 to avoid counting each diagonal twice (since each diagonal connects two vertices).\nTherefore, the number of diagonals is $\\frac{7 \\cdot 4}{2}=\\boxed{14}$.\nThe answer is: 14"}
