{"id": "general_smoltalk_2300_98352", "question": "Twenty-seven increased by twice a number is X. What is the number?\nIf we know the answer to the above question is 6, what is the value of unknown variable X?", "answer": "We are given that twenty-seven increased by twice a number is $X$.\nTo find the value of the number, we can set up an equation.\nWe can represent the number as $n$.\nThe equation can be written as:\n$27 + 2n = X$\nWe are given that the value of the number is 6, so we can substitute this value into the equation:\n$27 + 2(6) = X$\nSimplifying the equation, we have:\n$27 + 12 = X$\n$39 = X$\nThe value of $X$ is 39.\nThe answer is: 39"}
