{"id": "general_smoltalk_2300_509645", "question": "Write a function to find out whether a given year is a leap year or not.", "answer": "Here is a function in Python that takes in a year as an input parameter and returns whether it is a leap year or not:\n\n```python\ndef is_leap_year(year):\n    # Check if the year is evenly dividable by 4\n    if year % 4 == 0:\n        # Check if the year is evenly dividable by 100\n        if year % 100 == 0:\n            # Check if the year is evenly dividable by 400\n            if year % 400 == 0:\n                return True\n            else:\n                return False\n        else:\n            return True\n    else:\n        return False\n```\n\nThis function checks whether the given year is divisible by 4, 100, and 400. A year is considered a leap year if it is divisible by 4 and not divisible by 100, or if it is divisible by 400.\n\nFor example, if we use the following code to check if the year 2000 is a leap year, the result will be `True`:\n\n```python\nis_leap_year(2000)\n# Returns True\n```\n\nHowever, if we check if the year 1900 is a leap year, the result will be `False`:\n\n```python\nis_leap_year(1900)\n# Returns False\n```"}
