{"id": "general_smoltalk_2300_617362", "question": "Jerry Weller received 20,196 more votes than opponent John Pavich. If the total number of votes was 196,554 , find the number of votes for Jerry.", "answer": "Let's denote the number of votes Jerry Weller received as J and the number of votes John Pavich received as P. According to the information given:\n\nJ = P + 20,196\n\nWe also know that the total number of votes is 196,554, so:\n\nJ + P = 196,554\n\nNow we can substitute the first equation into the second equation:\n\n(P + 20,196) + P = 196,554\n\nCombine like terms:\n\n2P + 20,196 = 196,554\n\nSubtract 20,196 from both sides to solve for P:\n\n2P = 196,554 - 20,196\n2P = 176,358\n\nNow divide by 2 to find P:\n\nP = 176,358 / 2\nP = 88,179\n\nNow that we have P, we can find J by adding 20,196 to P:\n\nJ = P + 20,196\nJ = 88,179 + 20,196\nJ = 108,375\n\nSo, Jerry Weller received $\\boxed{108,375}$  votes."}
