iendships, and feel more connected to their community. This can be especially important for seniors, who may be looking for ways to stay active, engaged, and connected.\n\nUltimately, incorporating dance or movement into a library setting can help redefine the notion of what a library is and what it can offer. By embracing movement and creativity, libraries can become vibrant community hubs that nurture the body, mind, and spirit."}
