{"id": "general_smoltalk_2300_79313", "question": "The 210th anniversary of the birth of novelist Charles Dickens was celebrated on February 7, 2022, a Monday. On what day of the week was Dickens born?\nA) Wednesday\nB) Thursday\nC) Friday\nD) Saturday\nE) Sunday", "answer": "1. **Identify the number of leap years and regular years in 210 years:**\n   - A leap year occurs every 4 years, except for years divisible by 100 but not by 400. Thus, in a span of 210 years from 1812 to 2022:\n     - Every 4th year is a leap year: $\\frac{210}{4} = 52.5 \\approx 52$ potential leap years.\n     - Exclude years divisible by 100 but not by 400: 1900 is such a year within this range.\n     - Therefore, the actual count of leap years is $52 - 1 = 51$.\n     - The remaining years are regular years: $210 - 51 = 159$.\n\n2. **Calculate the total number of days to move back:**\n   - Each regular year contributes 1 day backward modulo 7 (since $365 \\equiv 1 \\pmod{7}$).\n   - Each leap year contributes 2 days backward modulo 7 (since $366 \\equiv 2 \\pmod{7}$).\n   - Total backward movement in days is $159 \\times 1 + 51 \\times 2 = 159 + 102 = 261$ days.\n\n3. **Reduce the total days backward modulo 7:**\n   - Calculate $261 \\mod 7 = 3$.\n   - This means moving 3 days backward from Monday.\n\n4. **Determine the day of the week 3 days before Monday:**\n   - Counting backward from Monday: Sunday (1), Saturday (2), Friday (3).\n\nThus, Charles Dickens was born on a $\\text{Friday}$.\nThe final answer is $\\boxed{C}$"}
