{"id": "general_smoltalk_2300_352342", "question": "Harper drinks a 1/2 bottle of mineral water per day.  She buys the mineral water by the case at a big box store.  They come x bottles to a case and are currently on sale for $12.00.  If she wants to buy enough cases to last her 240 days, She will spend 60. What is the value of unknown variable x?", "answer": "To solve this problem, we need to determine the value of x, which represents the number of bottles in each case of mineral water.\nLet's break down the information given:\nAmount of mineral water consumed per day: 1/2 bottle\nNumber of bottles in each case: x\nCost of each case on sale: $12.00\nNumber of days for which Harper wants to buy enough cases: 240\nTotal cost of cases to last 240 days: $60.00\nWe can set up the equation as follows:\nAmount of mineral water consumed per day * Number of days = Number of bottles consumed in total\n1/2 * 240 = Number of bottles consumed in total\nLet's simplify and solve for the number of bottles consumed in total:\n240/2 = Number of bottles consumed in total\n120 = Number of bottles consumed in total\nNext, we can set up the equation to calculate the number of cases needed:\nNumber of bottles consumed in total / Number of bottles in each case = Number of cases needed\n120 / x = Number of cases needed\nFinally, we can set up the equation to calculate the total cost of the cases:\nNumber of cases needed * Cost of each case = Total cost of cases\n(Number of bottles consumed in total / Number of bottles in each case) * $12.00 = $60.00\nLet's simplify and solve for x:\n(120 / x) * $12.00 = $60.00\n12 * 120 = x * $60.00\n1440 = 60x\nTo isolate x, we divide both sides of the equation by 60:\n1440 / 60 = x\n24 = x\nThe value of x is 24.\n#### 24\nThe answer is: 24"}
