{"id": "general_smoltalk_2300_98386", "question": "Write a program in Java that will translate english words into their corresponding pig latin representations. Pig Latin is a playful language game that alters words in English by moving the first consonant (or consonant cluster) to the end of the word and adding the sound \"ay\" to the end of the word. If the word begins with a vowel, you just add \"way\".", "answer": "Here is a simple Java program that translates English words to Pig Latin:\n\n```java\nimport java.util.Scanner;\n\npublic class PigLatinTranslator {\n\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\n        Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);\n        System.out.println(\"Enter a word to translate to Pig Latin:\");\n        String word = scanner.nextLine();\n        scanner.close();\n\n        System.out.println(\"Pig Latin translation: \" + translateToPigLatin(word));\n    }\n\n    public static String translateToPigLatin(String word) {\n        word = word.toLowerCase();\n        if (startsWithVowel(word)) {\n            return word + \"way\";\n        } else {\n            int vowelIndex = findFirstVowelIndex(word);\n            String consonantCluster = word.substring(0, vowelIndex);\n            String restOfWord = word.substring(vowelIndex);\n            return restOfWord + consonantCluster + \"ay\";\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static boolean startsWithVowel(String word) {\n        return word.charAt(0) == 'a' || word.charAt(0) == 'e' || word.charAt(0) == 'i' || word.charAt(0) == 'o' || word.charAt(0) == 'u';\n    }\n\n    public static int findFirstVowelIndex(String word) {\n        for (int i = 0; i < word.length(); i++) {\n            char c = word.charAt(i);\n            if (c == 'a' || c == 'e' || c == 'i' || c == 'o' || c == 'u') {\n                return i;\n            }\n        }\n        return 0; // should not happen for English words\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThis program asks for a word as input and then prints its Pig Latin translation. The `translateToPigLatin` method checks if the word starts with a vowel and appends \"way\" to it. If it starts with a consonant, it moves the consonant cluster to the end and appends \"ay\". The `startsWithVowel` and `findFirstVowelIndex` methods are helper methods to check for vowels. Note that this program assumes the input word only contains letters and does not handle punctuation or numbers."}
