{"id": "general_smoltalk_2300_834108", "question": "Write a python function that calculates the amount of money spent on groceries by analyzing a list of products purchased and their respective prices. The function should also apply an 8 percent sales tax on the total cost of the items. \n\nHere is a dictionary containing a list of products and their prices.\nproducts = {\n    \"milk\": 2.99,\n    \"eggs\": 1.49,\n    \"bread\": 2.49,\n    \"chicken\": 5.99,\n    \"rice\": 1.99\n}", "answer": "Here's a Python function that calculates the total cost of groceries, including an 8% sales tax:\n\n```python\ndef calculate_grocery_cost(products, items_purchased):\n    subtotal = sum(products[item] for item in items_purchased)\n    tax = subtotal * 0.08\n    total_cost = subtotal + tax\n    return subtotal, tax, total_cost\n\nproducts = {\n    \"milk\": 2.99,\n    \"eggs\": 1.49,\n    \"bread\": 2.49,\n    \"chicken\": 5.99,\n    \"rice\": 1.99\n}\n\nitems_purchased = [\"milk\", \"eggs\", \"bread\", \"chicken\"]\nsubtotal, tax, total_cost = calculate_grocery_cost(products, items_purchased)\n\nprint(f\"Subtotal: ${subtotal:.2f}\")\nprint(f\"Tax (8%): ${tax:.2f}\")\nprint(f\"Total cost: ${total_cost:.2f}\")\n```\n\nIn this code:\n\n- The `calculate_grocery_cost` function takes a dictionary of products and a list of items purchased as input.\n- It calculates the subtotal by summing the prices of the items purchased.\n- It calculates the tax by multiplying the subtotal by 8% (or 0.08).\n- It calculates the total cost by adding the subtotal and tax.\n- The function returns the subtotal, tax, and total cost.\n- The example usage demonstrates how to call the function with the provided products dictionary and a list of items purchased, and prints the results to the console."}
{"id": "general_smoltalk_2300_299036", "question": "Create a C++ program to print the unique elements of a sorted array. \n1. Create a function in C++ to find the unique element in an array.\n2. In the main function create an array with some sample values and use the function to print the unique element.\n\nBelow is the format for inputting the code\n```cpp\n// your code here\n```", "answer": "```cpp\n#include <iostream>\nusing namespace std;\n\n// Function to print unique elements in a sorted array\nvoid printUniqueElements(int arr[], int size) {\n    if (size == 0) {\n        cout << \"Array is empty\" << endl;\n        return;\n    }\n\n    int current = arr[0];\n    cout << current << \" \";\n\n    for (int i = 1; i < size; i++) {\n        if (arr[i] != current) {\n            cout << arr[i] << \" \";\n            current = arr[i];\n        }\n    }\n}\n\nint main() {\n    int arr[] = {1, 1, 2, 2, 3, 4, 5, 5, 5, 6};\n    int size = sizeof(arr) / sizeof(arr[0]);\n\n    cout << \"Original array: \";\n    for (int i = 0; i < size; i++) {\n        cout << arr[i] << \" \";\n    }\n    cout << endl;\n\n    cout << \"Unique elements: \";\n    printUniqueElements(arr, size);\n\n    return 0;\n}\n```"}
