{"id": "general_smoltalk_2300_1039714", "question": "How many positive 3-digit numbers are divisible by 7?", "answer": "The smallest 3-digit number divisible by 7 is 105, and the largest is 994.\nWe can count the number of multiples of 7 by finding the difference between the largest and smallest multiples and adding 1.\nUsing this method, there are $\\frac{994-105}{7}+1=\\frac{889}{7}+1=127+1=128$ positive 3-digit numbers divisible by 7.\nSo, there are $\\boxed{128}$ positive 3-digit numbers divisible by 7.\nThe answer is: 128"}
