{"id": "general_smoltalk_2300_1012684", "question": "The slope of the line $x=1$ is ______.", "answer": "The given line is $x=1$, which is a vertical line. Vertical lines are perpendicular to the horizontal axis (the $x$-axis). The concept of slope is tied to the rate of change of $y$ with respect to $x$. For a vertical line, this change is undefined because the line does not move horizontally, only vertically. Therefore, the slope of a vertical line is not expressed in terms of degrees but is considered to be undefined.\n\n- Given: Line $x=1$\n- Observation: This line is vertical and perpendicular to the $x$-axis.\n- Conclusion: The slope of a vertical line is undefined.\n\nTherefore, the correct statement about the slope of the line $x=1$ should be: $\\boxed{\\text{undefined}}$."}
