{"id": "general_smoltalk_2300_451474", "question": "Write a Python function `decompose_values` to convert a given tuple of mixed-type values into a stream of single-type values. The function should accept a tuple of mixed-type values and return a stream of single-type values. Every value in the returned stream should be a string representing a single value. For numerical values, the function should produce the string representation of the value. For booleans, the function should produce `true` or `false`. For strings, the function should produce the string itself without quotes.", "answer": "```python\ndef decompose_values(values):\n    single_type_values = []\n    for value in values:\n        if isinstance(value, str):\n            single_type_values.append(value)\n        elif isinstance(value, bool):\n            single_type_values.append('true' if value else 'false')\n        else:\n            single_type_values.append(str(value))\n    return single_type_values\n```"}
