100-$300 per person for each leg of the journey. Alternatively, a guided tour package might include these transportation costs, making it a convenient option.\n\nTo prioritize visiting main attractions, consider purchasing a city pass or attraction bundle for each city. These passes can provide skip-the-line access and save you around 20-30% on individual attraction tickets. Allocate around $500-$800 for attraction tickets and city passes.\n\nGiven these estimates, you can allocate your budget as follows: flights ($3,000-$4,000), accommodations ($1,500-$2,500), transportation ($500-$1,000), and attractions ($500-$800). This leaves you with a buffer for food, miscellaneous expenses, and unexpected costs.\n\nA guided tour package might be a viable option if you prefer a hassle-free experience and don't mind paying a premium for convenience. However, planning everything yourself can be more cost-effective and provide flexibility in your itinerary.\n\nTo get started, research flights from New York City to London, Paris, and Rome, considering your preferred travel dates. Look for budget-friendly accommodation options, and explore city passes and attraction bundles for each city. If you prefer a guided tour package, research reputable tour operators and compare their prices with your estimated costs."}
