ey the notion of targeting a wide spectrum of legal issues.\n\n4. Assess whether the hypothesis follows from the premise:\n   Based on the comparison of key ideas, the hypothesis seems to be a condensed and slightly less specific version of the premise. While there are differences between the words \"multiculturally competent\" and \"multiculturally literate\" and the scope of legal issues mentioned, the fundamental concepts remain similar. In this sense, if the premise is true, it can be argued that the hypothesis is likely true, as well, with the understanding that it presents a more generalized view of the same ideas."}
