{"id": "general_smoltalk_2300_313674", "question": "LaKeisha is mowing lawns to raise money for a collector set of books. She charges $.10 for every square foot of lawn. She has already mowed three 20 x 15 foot lawns and needs to mow 600 more square feet to earn enough money. How much does the book set cost?", "answer": "First, let's calculate the total square footage LaKeisha has already mowed:\n\nEach lawn is 20 x 15 feet, so the area of one lawn is:\n20 feet * 15 feet = 300 square feet\n\nShe has mowed three lawns, so the total area she has mowed so far is:\n3 lawns * 300 square feet per lawn = 900 square feet\n\nNow, let's calculate how much money she has earned from mowing these three lawns:\n\nShe charges $.10 for every square foot, so for 900 square feet, she has earned:\n900 square feet * $.10 per square foot = $90\n\nLaKeisha still needs to mow 600 more square feet to earn enough money for the book set. Let's calculate how much more money she will earn from mowing this additional area:\n\n600 square feet * $.10 per square foot = $60\n\nNow, let's add the money she has already earned to the money she will earn from the additional 600 square feet:\n\n$90 (already earned) + $60 (additional earnings) = $150\n\nTherefore, the collector set of books costs $\\boxed{\\$150}$ ."}
