\\frac{35}{6} \\) circles.\n   - For the additional \\((11^{th})\\) hour, mosquito completes \\( \\frac{1}{12} \\) circles before returning to the starting point.\n   - Over 12th hour, it completes \\(1\\) full circle as it completes a lap.\n\n   Therefore, total circle covered in 12 hours:\n   \\[\n   = \\frac{35}{6} + \\frac{1}{12}+1 =\\frac{70}{12} + \\frac{1}{12} + \\frac{12}{12}= \\frac{83}{12} \\text{ circles}\n   \\]\n\n5. **Fly's movement**:\n   - Fly calculates similarly but results swapped as minutes hand faster by factor 12.\n   - Each 2 hours covers \\( = (\\frac{1}{6} + \\frac{10}{12}) =\\frac{2}{12) + \\frac{10}{12} = \\frac{12}{12} = 1 \\text{ circle}.\n   - Over 10 hours: \\((1 circles *5) = 5 circles.\n   - Adding additional total: 12 hours\n   \\[ \n   =73 \\\\\n6+\\frac{73}{12}\n\\]\n\nSo, the final ratio:\n\n6. **Conclusion**: \n    \\[\n    \\boxed{\\frac{83}{73}}\n    \\]"}
