{"id": "general_smoltalk_2300_1032179", "question": "Implement a queue data structure using Python. Provide an explanation of the implementation. \n\n```python\nclass Queue:\n    pass\n```", "answer": "Here's an implementation of a queue data structure in Python:\n```python\nclass Queue:\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.items = []\n\n    def enqueue(self, item):\n        self.items.append(item)\n\n    def dequeue(self):\n        if self.is_empty():\n            raise IndexError(\"Cannot dequeue from an empty queue\")\n        return self.items.pop(0)\n\n    def is_empty(self):\n        return len(self.items) == 0\n\n    def size(self):\n        return len(self.items)\n\n    def peek(self):\n        if self.is_empty():\n            raise IndexError(\"Cannot peek into an empty queue\")\n        return self.items[0]\n\n    def __str__(self):\n        return str(self.items)\n```\nExplanation:\n\n*   We implement the queue using a list (`self.items`).\n*   The `enqueue` method adds an item to the end of the queue, which is equivalent to appending to the list.\n*   The `dequeue` method removes an item from the front of the queue, which is equivalent to popping from the beginning of the list. It raises an `IndexError` if the queue is empty.\n*   The `is_empty` method checks whether the queue is empty by checking the length of the list.\n*   The `size` method returns the number of items in the queue, which is equivalent to the length of the list.\n*   The `peek` method returns the item at the front of the queue without removing it, which is equivalent to accessing the first element of the list. It raises an `IndexError` if the queue is empty.\n*   The `__str__` method returns a string representation of the queue, which is useful for printing.\n\nExample usage:\n\n```python\nq = Queue()\nq.enqueue(1)\nq.enqueue(2)\nq.enqueue(3)\nprint(q)  # Output: [1, 2, 3]\nprint(q.dequeue())  # Output: 1\nprint(q)  # Output: [2, 3]\nprint(q.peek())  # Output: 2\nprint(q.size())  # Output: 2\nprint(q.is_empty())  # Output: False\n```"}
