 14t + 30 \\), \\( t \\) is the independent variable, but the rate of increase is incorrect.\n- C: \\( T = 14t - 16 \\), \\( t \\) is the independent variable, but the equation does not match the observed data.\n- D: \\( T = 30t - 14 \\), \\( T \\) is the dependent variable, but the equation is incorrect.\n\nThe correct choice that matches our observation and equation is A: \\( T = 7t + 30 \\), with \\( T \\) as the dependent variable.\n\nTherefore, the answer is $\\boxed{\\text{A}}$."}
