o £80,000.", "answer": "To celebrate 150 years of skiing in Switzerland, Christie's in London will host The Ski Sale in January, featuring a collection of vintage ski posters from Switzerland and other popular ski destinations. The auction includes iconic designs by renowned artists such as Carl Moos, Emil Cardinaux, and Martin Peikert, capturing the glamour and beauty of ski resorts like St Moritz, Davos, Zermatt, and Gstaad. Highlights include Carl Moos' St Moritz poster, estimated to fetch between £18,000 and £22,000, and Emil Cardinaux's Davos sketch, with an estimate of £12,000 to £18,000. The sale also features posters from France, Italy, Austria, Germany, Norway, and Australia, as well as US and Canadian resorts. Nicolette Tomkinson, Head of the Ski Sale, notes that the popularity of these posters has grown among private collectors who use them to decorate their chalets, particularly those depicting well-known and glamorous ski destinations. The auction will also include 25 lots of vintage Louis Vuitton travel luggage, with estimates ranging from £800 to £80,000."}
