erpiece featuring sugar flowers that change colors throughout the night.\n\nThese ideas are just the starting point, but they're sure to spark some creativity and inspire a truly one-of-a-kind wedding reception that will leave a lasting impression on the couple and their guests. What would you like to add or explore further?"}
{"id": "general_smoltalk_2300_845138", "question": "Create an analogy for black hole", "answer": "A black hole could be thought of as a cosmic vacuum cleaner, much in the same way that a vacuum cleaner sucks in dirt and dust, a black hole sucks in everything that gets too close to its event horizon, including light. Once something enters the event horizon, there’s no coming back, just as the dirt that goes into the vacuum cleaner bag cannot be returned to the carpet. The stronger the vacuum cleaner, the more power it has to suck things in, and the same concept applies to black holes – the more massive the black hole, the greater its attractive force."}
