{"id": "general_smoltalk_2300_414238", "question": "Create a Python function that accepts a list of items and returns the most common item in that list. If there are multiple most common items, return a list of those items.\n\nExamples:\n- most_common_item([1, 2, 2, 3, 3, 3]) returns 3\n- most_common_item([1, 2, 2, 3, 3]) returns [2, 3]\n- most_common_item([1, 2, 3]) returns [1, 2, 3]\n\nHere's the basic structure for the function:\n\ndef most_common_item(lst):\n    # Implement your solution here\n    pass", "answer": "Here's a Python function that uses the built-in `Counter` class from the `collections` module to find the most common item(s) in a list:\n\n```python\nfrom collections import Counter\n\ndef most_common_item(lst):\n    counter = Counter(lst)\n    max_count = max(counter.values())\n    most_common = [item for item, count in counter.items() if count == max_count]\n    return most_common[0] if len(most_common) == 1 else most_common\n```\n\nThis function works as follows:\n\n- It uses `Counter` to count the occurrences of each item in the list.\n- It finds the maximum count.\n- It creates a list of items that have the maximum count.\n- If there's only one most common item, it returns that item; otherwise, it returns the list of most common items."}
