{"id": "general_smoltalk_2300_675480", "question": "The motion equation of an object is $s= \\frac {1}{4}t^{4}-3$. What is the instantaneous velocity of the object when $t=5$?\nA: 5\nB: 25\nC: 125\nD: 625", "answer": "According to the problem, the motion equation of the object is $s= \\frac {1}{4}t^{4}-3$.\n\nTherefore, the derivative of $s$ with respect to $t$ is $s' = t^{3}$, which represents the velocity of the object.\n\nThus, when $t=5$, the instantaneous velocity of the object is $s'|_{t=5} = 125$.\n\nHence, the correct option is $\\boxed{C}$.\n\nTo solve this type of problem, the key is to be proficient in calculating derivatives and understanding the geometric meaning of the derivative as velocity, combined with correct calculation."}
