{"id": "general_smoltalk_2300_346363", "question": "The arithmetic mean of nine numbers is 54. If two numbers $u$ and $v$ are added to the list, the mean of the eleven-member list becomes 66. What is the mean of $u$ and $v$?", "answer": "The sum of the original nine numbers is $9 \\cdot 54 = 486$.\nThe sum of the eleven numbers is $11 \\cdot 66 = 726$.\nTherefore, the sum of $u$ and $v$ is $726-486=240$.\nSince we are finding the mean of $u$ and $v$, we divide the sum by 2, getting $\\frac{240}{2}=\\boxed{120}$.\nThe answer is: 120"}
