{"id": "general_smoltalk_2300_220019", "question": "If it takes 5 machines 5 minutes to make 5 widgets, how long would it take 100 machines to make 100 widgets?", "answer": "To solve this problem, let's first analyze the given information. Five machines can make 5 widgets in 5 minutes. This means that each machine can produce 1 widget in 5 minutes.\n\nIf we now have 100 machines working simultaneously, each machine still takes 5 minutes to produce 1 widget. The increased number of machines allows for a greater total output, but it doesn't change the production time per machine.\n\nSince all 100 machines work at the same time, they can produce 100 widgets in the same 5 minutes that it takes a single machine to produce 1 widget. Therefore, it would take 100 machines 5 minutes to make 100 widgets."}
