{"id": "general_smoltalk_2300_282014", "question": "I want to create a class in my program to model a computer's memory. Can you provide a solution on how to design this class?", "answer": "Certainly! Here's a solution that you can use to design your own class for computer memory.\n\n```java\npublic class Memory {\n    private int capacity;\n    private int size;\n\n    public Memory(int capacity) {\n        this.capacity = capacity;\n        this.size = 0;\n    }\n\n    public int getCapacity() {\n        return capacity;\n    }\n\n    public void setCapacity(int capacity) {\n        this.capacity = capacity;\n    }\n\n    public int getSize() {\n        return size;\n    }\n\n    public void setSize(int size) {\n        this.size = size;\n    }\n\n    public boolean isFull() {\n        return size == capacity;\n    }\n\n    public void write(int value) {\n        if (size < capacity) {\n            size++;\n        }\n    }\n\n    public void read() {\n        if (size > 0) {\n            size--;\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\nIn this solution, the `Memory` class has two private instance variables: `capacity` and `size`. The constructor `Memory(int capacity)` initializes the memory with the given capacity and sets the size to 0.\n\nThere are several methods provided in this class. The `getCapacity()` method returns the current capacity of the memory. The `setCapacity(int capacity)` method allows you to change the capacity of the memory.\n\nThe `getSize()` method returns the current size of the memory, while the `setSize(int size)` method allows you to set the size of the memory.\n\nThe `isFull()` method checks if the memory is full by comparing the size with the capacity. It returns `true` if the size is equal to the capacity, indicating that the memory is full.\n\nThe `write(int value)` method is used to write data into the memory. It increases the size of the memory by 1 if the current size is less than the capacity.\n\nThe `read()` method is used to read data from the memory. It decreases the size of the memory by 1 if the current size is greater than 0.\n\nYou can incorporate this `Memory` class into your program to model the memory of a computer."}
