0; i < 10; i++) {\n        printf(\"%d\\n\", arr[i]);\n    }\n\n    return 0;\n}\n```\n\nNote: In the C code, we use `qsort` function from the C standard library for sorting the array. Also, we use `srand` and `rand` functions to generate random numbers. The `compare` function is used as a comparator for the `qsort` function."}
