{"id": "general_smoltalk_2300_512085", "question": "For a given `event` object with a `.start_time` attribute, write a Python function that computes the event status based on the current time and the start time of the event. Here are the conditions and the corresponding status values:\n\n1. If the current time is before the start time, the status is `NOT STARTED`.\n2. If the current time is later than the start time but less than 1 hour later, the status is `STARTING SOON`.\n3. If the current time is later than 1 hour after the start time but less than 48 hours later, the status is `LIVE`.\n4. If the current time is later than 48 hours after the start time, the status is `ENDED`.\n\nThe function should return the computed status value as a string.", "answer": "To compute the event status based on the given event object, we'll need to access the `.start_time` attribute. We'll also need to use the current time to determine when the event is in progress. Based on the conditions provided, here are the steps to compute the event status:\n\n1. Access the `.start_time` attribute of the event object.\n2. Determine the current time using the `datetime` module.\n3. Compare the current time with the start time of the event to determine the status.\n4. Use `if-else` statements to check if the current time is before the start time, if it's later than the start time, if it's later than 1 hour after the start time, and so on.\n5. Assign the corresponding status value based on the comparison results.\n\nHere's how you could implement the function using the steps above:\n\n```python\nimport datetime\n\ndef compute_event_status(event):\n    start_time = event.start_time\n    current_time = datetime.datetime.now()\n\n    if current_time < start_time:\n        return \"NOT STARTED\"\n    elif start_time <= current_time < start_time + datetime.timedelta(hours=1):\n        return \"STARTING SOON\"\n    elif start_time + datetime.timedelta(hours=1) <= current_time < start_time + datetime.timedelta(hours=48):\n        return \"LIVE\"\n    else:\n        return \"ENDED\"\n```"}
