{"id": "general_smoltalk_2300_920469", "question": "Write a Python function that takes a list of inputs and returns a list of outputs, where each output is the result of applying a function (f) to each input. The function should validate that all inputs are of the same type and return an error if any of the inputs is not of that type. The function should also catch any exception during the application of the function and return an error message instead of the output.", "answer": "Here is the implementation of the function:\n\n```python\ndef apply_f_to_inputs(f, inputs):\n    if not inputs:\n        return []\n    input_type = type(inputs[0])\n    for i in inputs[1:]:\n        if not isinstance(i, input_type):\n            return f\"Error: not all inputs are of type {input_type}.\"\n    outputs = []\n    for i in inputs:\n        try:\n            outputs.append(f(i))\n        except Exception as e:\n            return f\"Error: {str(e)}\"\n\n    return outputs\n```"}
