{"id": "general_smoltalk_2300_383432", "question": "Three friends ate a total of 8 pounds of fruit. Mario had 8 ounces of oranges, while Lydia ate 24 ounces of apples. Nicolai ate peaches. How many pounds of peaches did Nicolai eat?", "answer": "There are 16 ounces in 1 pound, so 8 pounds is equal to 8 * 16 = 128 ounces.\nMario ate 8 ounces of oranges and Lydia ate 24 ounces of apples, so together they ate 8 + 24 = 32 ounces.\nTherefore, Nicolai must have eaten 128 - 32 = 96 ounces of peaches.\nSince there are 16 ounces in 1 pound, Nicolai ate 96 / 16 = 6 pounds of peaches.\n#### 6\nThe answer is: 6"}
