{"id": "general_smoltalk_2300_334971", "question": "A highway maintenance team travels by car along a straight east-west road for maintenance. It is agreed that east is positive and west is negative. The distances traveled by the team from point $A$ to the end of work on a certain day are: $+12$, $-6$, $+4$, $-2$, $-8$, $+13$, $-2$ (unit: kilometers).<br/>$(1)$ At the end of work, is the team located to the east or west of point $A$? How far is it from point $A$?<br/>$(2)$ If the maintenance team returns to point $A$ in the end, and consumes $0.2$ liters of fuel per kilometer, how much fuel is consumed in total?", "answer": "### Solution:\n\n#### Part 1: Determining the Final Position\n\nTo find out whether the team is to the east or west of point $A$ and how far it is from point $A$, we sum up all the distances traveled considering east as positive and west as negative:\n\n\\[\n\\begin{align*}\n& (+12) + (-6) + (+4) + (-2) + (-8) + (+13) + (-2) \\\\\n&= 12 - 6 + 4 - 2 - 8 + 13 - 2 \\\\\n&= 11 \\text{ kilometers}.\n\\end{align*}\n\\]\n\nTherefore, at the end of work, the team is located to the east of point $A$ and is $\\boxed{11 \\text{ kilometers}}$ away from point $A$.\n\n#### Part 2: Calculating Total Fuel Consumption\n\nIf the maintenance team returns to point $A$, the total distance traveled includes all the distances mentioned plus the return distance to point $A$. The return distance is equal to the final distance from $A$ to the end point, which is $11$ kilometers. Therefore, the total distance traveled is:\n\n\\[\n\\begin{align*}\n& (12 + 6 + 4 + 2 + 8 + 13 + 2 + 11) \\\\\n&= 58 \\text{ kilometers}.\n\\end{align*}\n\\]\n\nGiven that the team consumes $0.2$ liters of fuel per kilometer, the total fuel consumption is:\n\n\\[\n58 \\times 0.2 = 11.6 \\text{ liters}.\n\\]\n\nThus, the total fuel consumption is $\\boxed{11.6 \\text{ liters}}$."}
