{"id": "general_smoltalk_2300_1022884", "question": "I have a string and I want to extract the last word from it. How can I do that in Python?", "answer": "You can achieve this by defining a function that takes a string as an argument and returns the last word of the string. Here's an example implementation:\n\n```python\ndef last_word(sentence):\n    return sentence.split(' ')[-1]\n```\n\nIn this code, the `split()` method is used to split the string into a list of words based on spaces (' '). Then, we access the last element of the list using the index `-1`, which corresponds to the last word in the string. Finally, the last word is returned as the result.\n\nYou can use this function by passing your string as an argument, and it will return the last word."}
