nder McQueen: Savage Beauty, shown at the Costume Institute of the Metropolitan Museum of Art in New York in 2011. Flower girls: With Sophia Loren on the front row and Dita von Teese on the catwalk, it was a theatrical and ambitious show today in Paris . Head start: It was all about the headgear at Gaultier's show today and racoons and butterflies were seemingly the inspiration .", "answer": "French fashion designer Jean Paul Gaultier presented his Spring/Summer 2014 Haute Couture collection in Paris, inspired by burlesque dancers. The show featured a glamorous and theatrical atmosphere, a departure from Gaultier's typically controversial themes. American burlesque dancer and model Dita Von Teese, 41, made a surprise appearance, walking the catwalk in a risqué butterfly-inspired outfit. The event also marked a successful week for Gaultier, as his exhibition, \"The Fashion World of Jean Paul Gaultier: From the Sidewalk to the Catwalk,\" is set to open in Paris in April 2015. The exhibition, which has toured several cities including Montreal, Dallas, San Francisco, Madrid, Rotterdam, and New York, has broken fashion exhibition records with over a million visitors. The show's front row included celebrities like Sophia Loren, adding to the star-studded and ambitious presentation."}
