e shopping, historic cafes, and beautiful architecture. Take your time wandering the streets, popping into cafes and shops, and soaking up the local atmosphere.\n\nThroughout your trip, remember to take breaks, indulge in delicious French cuisine, and enjoy the city's charming atmosphere. Don't worry too much about sticking to a rigid itinerary – Paris is a city that rewards flexibility and spontaneity. With this plan, you'll get a taste of the city's iconic landmarks, cultural attractions, and local neighborhoods, while still leaving room for exploration and discovery."}
