{"id": "general_smoltalk_2300_774025", "question": "Compute\n\\[\\begin{vmatrix} -5 & 3 \\\\ X & -4 \\end{vmatrix}. The answer is 8. What is the value of unknown variable X?", "answer": "To solve this problem, we need to determine the value of x, which represents the entry in the matrix.\nWe know that the determinant of the given matrix is 8.\nThe determinant of a 2x2 matrix with entries a, b, c, and d is given by the formula ad - bc.\nIn this case, we have -5*(-4) - (X*3) = 8.\nSimplifying the equation, we have 20 - 3X = 8.\nTo isolate X, we subtract 20 from both sides of the equation:\n20 - 20 - 3X = 8 - 20\n-3X = -12\nFinally, we divide both sides of the equation by -3 to solve for X:\nX = -12 / -3\nX = 4\nThe value of X is 4.\nThe answer is: 4"}
