{"id": "general_smoltalk_2300_979692", "question": "By . Louise Boyle . PUBLISHED: . 08:53 EST, 3 March 2014 . | . UPDATED: . 12:14 EST, 3 March 2014 . A 19-year-old college student who went missing four days ago has been found safe, police said today. Adeline Munguia, 19, who attends California State University, vanished last Thursday afternoon after reportedly meeting a man through dating app Tinder. A university spokesman told MailOnline today that the young woman was found with no signs of foul play in Montebello, California  - around eight miles from campus. Scroll down for video . Adeline Munguia, 19, who attends California State University vanished last Thursday but has since been found 'with no signs of foul play' The 19-year-old college student was last seen boarding a bus from Cal State University to downtown LA. She was found today in Montebello - eight miles from campus . The investigation was ongoing into where the student had been and why she had not made contact, the spokesman said on Monday. It is not clear if Miss Munguia, who is a California native, is from Montebello. Police earlier told MailOnline that Miss . Munguia lives in the college dorms and was last seen boarding an MTA bus . by herself from the campus to downtown LA. Detectives had been looking into all of her social networking activity for clues as to where the 19-year-old may have gone. The officer said it was not known if the young woman shared details of where she was going or if she was meeting anyone with friends. She was last seen on surveillance footage at 3.30pm on Thursday wearing a pink top with thin straps, black pants, open-toed shoes, carrying a beige and brown purse. She appeared to be looking down at her phone. Tinder is a dating app where potential dates connect with each other using profiles with limited information - typically just a few pictures, first name and how close geographically that person is to you. The app was launched by college students in California last year. Users 'swipe' a potential date's profile to the right on their smartphone screens if they like it. If two people do the same, they can then instant message each other to arrange a meeting. Tinder is a location-based social networking app that allows mutually interested users to link up with each other - simply by swiping the screen of their smartphone. It has quickly become known as a dating and even a 'hook up' app with 1.5billion profiles created since its launch. Of those, 5 million users are now accessing the app on average seven times per day. The app is currently generating 10 million matches every day. Tinder was launched at a campus party at the University of Southern California in 2012. It quickly spread to other college campuses before catching on among the wider population. It is most popular with men and women aged 18-35. Tinder is the fastest growing free dating app in the U.S. Once the app is downloaded on to a smart phone, users are asked by the app to allow access to their Facebook profile. An individual's Tinder profile (like the example pictured right) is then set up using just a first name, age, sexual orientation and a handful of photos. Immediately the faces of people between a certain age range and within a certain radius  appear on screen. Each individual uses their touch-screen phone to 'swipe' that face to the right if they like it, and left if they don't. The face profiles then continue in a steady stream. If both users swipe to 'like' each other, a chat box appears - and a private conversation can begin. The 19-year-old student was last seen at her college campus before boarding a bus to downtown Los Angeles .", "answer": "A 19-year-old college student, Adeline Munguia, who attends California State University, was found safe on March 3, 2014, four days after she went missing. Munguia was last seen on Thursday, February 27, boarding a bus from her campus to downtown Los Angeles. She was reportedly meeting a man she connected with through the dating app Tinder. Munguia was found in Montebello, California, about eight miles from her campus, with no signs of foul play. Police and university officials were investigating her social networking activity and the circumstances of her disappearance. The app Tinder, which Munguia used to meet the man, is a location-based social networking app that allows users to connect with others nearby by swiping profiles. It has gained significant popularity, especially among college students and young adults."}
{"id": "general_smoltalk_2300_614496", "question": "Write a story about a theme park that has been abandoned for decades and the legends surrounding it. \n\nThe name of the theme park is WonderWorld.", "answer": "WonderWorld, a place where laughter and excitement once filled the air, now stood as a haunting reminder of forgotten memories. Decades had passed since its gates last swung open, welcoming thrill-seekers and families to a world of wonder. The rickety rollercoaster, once the crown jewel of the park, now towered above the overgrown landscape like a skeletal giant, its tracks twisted and tangled in a mess of rust and vines.\n\nThe locals whispered tales of the park's dark past, of the tragic accidents and gruesome incidents that led to its downfall. They spoke of the 'Laughing Lady', a ghostly apparition said to haunt the abandoned funhouse, her maniacal cackle echoing through the empty halls. Some claimed to have seen her, a fleeting glimpse of a woman in a tattered clown suit, her face painted with a grotesque smile.\n\nOthers spoke of the 'Midnight Ride', a phantom train that allegedly roamed the deserted tracks under the light of the full moon. They said that on certain nights, when the wind was just right, you could hear the distant rumble of wheels on steel, the screams of delighted riders now transformed into mournful wails.\n\nThe bravest of souls would occasionally sneak into the park, seeking thrills and chills among the crumbling attractions. They would return with tales of strange occurrences: a Ferris wheel spinning on its own, the seats creaking ominously in the wind; a merry-go-round playing a haunting melody, the music seeming to come from nowhere and everywhere at once.\n\nDespite the passing years, WonderWorld remained a source of morbid fascination for the local community. They would gather at the park's entrance, sharing stories and legends around campfires, the flickering flames casting eerie shadows on the abandoned ticket booths.\n\nOne stormy night, a group of friends decided to explore the depths of WonderWorld, to uncover the secrets that lay hidden beneath the rust and decay. As they ventured deeper into the park, the wind howling through the empty corridors, they stumbled upon a hidden room beneath the funhouse. Inside, they found a dusty journal belonging to the park's former owner, a man named Silas.\n\nThe journal revealed a dark history, one of greed and ambition, of a man consumed by his own vision of wonder. Silas had made a pact with a mysterious investor, trading the park's soul for a chance at greatness. But as the years went by, the investor's true intentions became clear: to harvest the joy and laughter of the park's visitors, to feed a dark and malevolent force that lurked in the shadows.\n\nThe group of friends fled the park, the storm raging around them, the journal's secrets forever seared into their minds. As they looked back, they saw the lights of WonderWorld flicker to life, the rollercoaster's tracks glowing with an otherworldly energy. The Laughing Lady's cackle echoed through the night, and the Midnight Ride roared to life, its phantom train disappearing into the darkness, leaving behind a trail of screams and terror.\n\nFrom that day on, the locals avoided WonderWorld, fearful of the dark forces that lurked within its crumbling walls. But on certain nights, when the moon was full and the wind was just right, you could still hear the distant rumble of wheels on steel, the haunting melody of the merry-go-round, and the maniacal laughter of the Laughing Lady, beckoning in the brave and the foolhardy to experience the horrors of WonderWorld."}
{"id": "general_smoltalk_2300_884775", "question": "A company is looking to create a new sustainable product that incorporates recycled materials for its production. However, the product should be durable and not be perceived as being less valuable due to the incorporation of recycled materials. What ideas do you have for such a product? \n\nThink of an example product that would utilize recycled materials and how that product can be made to be durable and of high value to its users.", "answer": "Imagine a high-end, eco-friendly smartwatch made with recycled titanium from repurposed aircraft parts. The watch's face could be crafted from a durable, scratch-resistant glass made from crushed and re-melted glass bottles, reducing waste and the energy needed for new glass production. To enhance durability and luxury appeal, the watch strap could be designed from a unique blend of recycled silicone and sustainably sourced, naturally durable materials such as bamboo fibers.\n\nBy incorporating cutting-edge solar cell technology into the watch face, the product can be self-charging, eliminating the need for battery replacements and minimizing electronic waste. This innovative timepiece would not only showcase the possibilities of sustainable production but would also offer users a premium, eco-conscious accessory that rivals traditional luxury watches in both quality and design.\n\nTo further amplify the watch's exclusivity and allure, the company could collaborate with local artists to create unique, handcrafted packaging from repurposed materials such as recycled wood or repurposed cardboard, making each purchase a one-of-a-kind experience. The watch's packaging could also include a personalized message or certificate, detailing the origin of the recycled materials used and highlighting the positive environmental impact of the product's creation.\n\nAdditionally, the company could implement a take-back program, allowing customers to return their used smartwatches for proper recycling and upgrading to newer models, ensuring the continuous reduction of electronic waste and fostering a loyal customer base committed to the brand's eco-friendly mission."}
